<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1146,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1146,1171]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Type series.</emphasis>
Holotype: male UMUT RA32562 (
<figureCitation box="[691,767,1146,1171]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
A–B’, F–K, 2A–B), collected from type locality. Paratypes: male: UMUT RA32565 (
<figureCitation box="[436,515,1182,1207]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[173,1424,245,1595]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1611]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32559): (A) LV, (E 1 – E 3) normal sieve pores, (E 4 – E 5) normal simple pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32561): (B) dorsal view. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32560): (C) muscle scars, (D) top left hinge, bottom right hinge. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32565): (F) LV, (G) RV, (K 1) normal simple pore, (K 2 – K 4) sieve pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32567): (H) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32566): (I) top left hinge, bottom right hinge, (J) muscle scars. Scale bars: A – B, D, F – I = 100 µm; C, J = 50 µm; E 1 – E 5, K 1 – K 4 = 5 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257881/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
F–G, K1–K4), females: UMUT RA32564 (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1068,1182,1207]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C–E, L), UMUT RA32566 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[173,1424,245,1595]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1611]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32559): (A) LV, (E 1 – E 3) normal sieve pores, (E 4 – E 5) normal simple pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32561): (B) dorsal view. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32560): (C) muscle scars, (D) top left hinge, bottom right hinge. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32565): (F) LV, (G) RV, (K 1) normal simple pore, (K 2 – K 4) sieve pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32567): (H) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32566): (I) top left hinge, bottom right hinge, (J) muscle scars. Scale bars: A – B, D, F – I = 100 µm; C, J = 50 µm; E 1 – E 5, K 1 – K 4 = 5 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257881/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
Fig. 
<date box="[151,179,1219,1243]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328" value="2010-01">10</date>
</figureCitation>
I–J), 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1416807288" collectionCode="UMUT" country="Iceland" county="The" location="University" municipality="University Museum" pageId="3" pageNumber="328" specimenCount="3" stateProvince="Tokyo" typeStatus="paratype">
<collectionCode box="[240,323,1219,1242]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kzwh-7f0x" name="University Museum, University of Tokyo" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">UMUT</collectionCode>
RA32567 (
<figureCitation box="[462,547,1218,1243]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[173,1424,245,1595]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1611]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32559): (A) LV, (E 1 – E 3) normal sieve pores, (E 4 – E 5) normal simple pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32561): (B) dorsal view. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32560): (C) muscle scars, (D) top left hinge, bottom right hinge. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male paratype (UMUT RA 32565): (F) LV, (G) RV, (K 1) normal simple pore, (K 2 – K 4) sieve pores. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32567): (H) dorsal view. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32566): (I) top left hinge, bottom right hinge, (J) muscle scars. Scale bars: A – B, D, F – I = 100 µm; C, J = 50 µm; E 1 – E 5, K 1 – K 4 = 5 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257881/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
H). 
<typeStatus box="[594,703,1219,1243]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Paratypes</typeStatus>
were collected from Tavewa 
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1123,1218,1243]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Island</collectingCountry>
(P1, 
<figureCitation box="[1191,1260,1218,1243]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1304,1326]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1272]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,267,1282]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. P 1 – P 6: present study specimen collection sites. B 1 – B 3: collection sites for Xestoleberis variegata and Xestoleberis curta by Brady (1890). Refer to Table 1 for site details. Color-coded circles indicating the geographical distribution of Fijian Xestoleberis species (seven new species described by the present paper and two species reported by Brady (1890 )). Ocean depth contours and the fast flowing Bligh Water currents are also illustrated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208331/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, Table 1). 
<collectingCounty box="[1392,1436,1218,1243]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">The</collectingCounty>
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1254,1279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[322,429,1255,1279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">paratypes</typeStatus>
are deposited at the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[706,941,1254,1279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">University Museum</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8B57EE20FFF7B309B4CC3C7C43B58BFD:062109EDFFF7B30EB7993CA947478CC5" box="[962,1080,1254,1279]" country="Iceland" county="The" municipality="University Museum" name="University" pageId="3" pageNumber="328" stateProvince="Tokyo">University</location>
of 
<collectingRegion box="[1136,1210,1254,1279]" country="Japan" name="Tokyo" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Tokyo</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1416807285" collectionCode="UMUT" country="Japan" location="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="328" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="paratype">
<collectingCountry box="[1230,1297,1255,1278]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Valves on paleontological paper/cavity slides and soft parts mounted on glass slides. Additional 
<typeStatus box="[1123,1230,1291,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">paratypes</typeStatus>
preserved in 70% ethanol: two males and three females 
<collectionCode box="[574,657,1327,1350]" country="Japan" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kzwh-7f0x" name="University Museum, University of Tokyo" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">UMUT</collectionCode>
RA32563.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1146,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,1362,1387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
<typeStatus box="[199,258,1362,1387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
A coral rubble, coarse sand coast along the open coastline of Korotogo, 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1238,1362,1387]" name="Fiji" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Viti</collectingCountry>
Levu 
<collectingCountry box="[1313,1381,1362,1387]" name="Iceland" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Island</collectingCountry>
(P3, 
<figureCitation box="[151,209,1398,1423]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1304,1326]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1272]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,267,1282]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. P 1 – P 6: present study specimen collection sites. B 1 – B 3: collection sites for Xestoleberis variegata and Xestoleberis curta by Brady (1890). Refer to Table 1 for site details. Color-coded circles indicating the geographical distribution of Fijian Xestoleberis species (seven new species described by the present paper and two species reported by Brady (1890 )). Ocean depth contours and the fast flowing Bligh Water currents are also illustrated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208331/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig 1</figureCitation>
, Table 1); habitat: a short red alga (
<taxonomicName box="[609,852,1398,1422]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Galaxauraceae" genus="Galaxaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="328" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="divaricata">
<emphasis box="[609,852,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Galaxaura divaricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1146,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis box="[199,261,1435,1458]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">eccus</emphasis>
is Latin for beak; the upper outside edges of the proximal structure of the hemipenes are shaped like beaks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="328" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1146,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1506,1531]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace with widely rounded posterior and anterior ends. Marginal pores line edges of carapace; anterior edges of carapace have branching pore canals. Coloration in living specimens transparent with opaque patches. BO short segment with numerous fine terminating setae. Ejaculatory ducts have irregular arrangements with inward exists. Furca reduced to short seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="329" pageId="3" pageNumber="328" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1146,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1650,1675]" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Description.</emphasis>
Carapace reniform and strongly inflated (
<figureCitation box="[822,900,1650,1675]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,1079,1773]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[149,1434,1037,1799]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male holotype (A) RV, (B) LV (UMUT RA 32562). Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (C) RV, (D) LV (UMUT RA 32550). Xestoleberis gracilariaii n. sp. Male holotype (E) RV, (F) LV (UMUT RA 32531). Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Male holotype (G) RV, (H) LV (UMUT RA 32556). Xestoleberis natuvuensis n. sp. Female paratype (I) RV, (J) LV (UMUT RA 32543). Xestoleberis penna n. sp. Female paratype (K) RV, (L) LV (UMUT RA 32538). Xestoleberis petrosa n. sp. Male holotype (M) RV, (N) LV (UMUT RA 32524). Scale bar: 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208332/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A–B, 10A,–E5). Maximum valve length range: 372 µm–460 µm, maximum valve height range: 240 µm–274 µm (
<tableCitation box="[892,978,1686,1711]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="15.[151,235,152,174]" captionText="TABLE 2. Maximum lengths and heights of the type specimens for the seven new Fijian Xestoleberis species described in this paper." pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Maximum height at mid-length. Dorsal margin convex, ventral indentation about halfway along carapace. Wide anterior and moderate width posterior vestibula. Merodont hinge; median groove and bar of hinge finely locellate. Normal and (possibly) exocrine sieve pores scattered over carapace, simple pores along ventral and anterior edges. Scar pattern: posterior row of four adductor scars, single anterior scar trefoil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1146,2035]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,967]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="329" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">
An1 with six podomeres; first two big, wide and rectangular, third–sixth small and quadrate (
<figureCitation box="[1289,1357,1866,1891]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A–A’). Third podomere with one dorsal apical seta and fourth and fifth podomeres with one short and one long dorsal apical setae. Terminating setae of sixth podomere: one slender and round tipped, and three fine (one long and two short). An2 with one dorsal and two ventral medial setae and one stout ventral apical seta of second endopodite podomere (
<figureCitation box="[281,350,2010,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="328">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B–B’). No prominent serrations on two terminating claws. Md coxa with six pointed and two lobate teeth and three fine setae (
<figureCitation box="[518,583,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C–E). Palp with four podomeres, first podomere with one fine ventral apical seta, second podomere with two long ventral and one long dorsal apical setae, two short medial setae at junction of second and third podomeres, third podomere with one ventral and five (four long and one short) dorsal apical setae, fourth podomere with one stout terminating claw and one fine terminating setae. Exopodite with at least two long setuled setae. 
<collectingCountry box="[307,346,296,319]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Mx</collectingCountry>
with two segmented palp; first segment with four distal dorsal-apical setae and second with three terminating setae (
<figureCitation box="[368,438,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
F–F’). Branchial plate with 11 setuled setae. BO is symmetrical; short segment with numerous fine terminating setae (
<figureCitation box="[526,593,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
G).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">
Basal setal formula for L5 1+1:2:1 and L6 and L7 1+1:1:1 (
<figureCitation box="[865,930,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
H–J). Terminating claws L5, L6 and L7 short and curved. Hp with asymmetrical, trigonal to sub-trigonal distal processes: one with wide, rounded end, other with tapered end (
<figureCitation box="[301,369,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1721]" captionTargetBox="[189,1391,233,1640]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Xestoleberis becca. n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32562): (A) An 1, (A’) terminating An 1 setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (F) Mx, (F’) Mx palp, (G) BO. (H) L 5, (I) L 6, (J) L 7, (K) Hp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32564): (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (L) Furca. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208333/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
K). Proximal ends of the capsules almost right-angled and proximal support structure shaped like pair of beaks placed back to back. Furca short fine seta on small rounded base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="329" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[361,573,548,572]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becca" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[361,573,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Xestoleberis becca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[582,647,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[582,647,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
occurs in four locations; including the 
<typeStatus box="[1100,1198,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">holotype</typeStatus>
locality, this species also occurs in the southeast of Tavewa 
<collectingCountry box="[592,660,583,608]" name="Iceland" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Island</collectingCountry>
(P1), Korovou, Naviti 
<collectingCountry box="[922,990,583,608]" name="Iceland" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Island</collectingCountry>
(P2), and Viani, Vanua Levu (P5) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1304,1326]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,267,1272]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,267,1282]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. P 1 – P 6: present study specimen collection sites. B 1 – B 3: collection sites for Xestoleberis variegata and Xestoleberis curta by Brady (1890). Refer to Table 1 for site details. Color-coded circles indicating the geographical distribution of Fijian Xestoleberis species (seven new species described by the present paper and two species reported by Brady (1890 )). Ocean depth contours and the fast flowing Bligh Water currents are also illustrated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208331/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, Table 1). In addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[529,627,620,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">holotype</typeStatus>
habitat, specimen collections were also made from short red algae (
<taxonomicName box="[160,319,656,680]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Pterocladiaceae" genus="Pterocladiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,319,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Pterocladiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<taxonomicName box="[412,645,656,680]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Gracilariaceae" genus="Gracilaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gigartinales" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="maramae">
<emphasis box="[412,645,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Gracilaria maramae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a tall brown alga (
<taxonomicName box="[872,994,656,679]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fucales" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Heterokontophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[872,994,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Sargassum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.) and sediments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="329" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,532,692,716]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becca" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[322,532,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Xestoleberis becca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[540,603,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,603,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Titterton &amp; Whatley, 2005" authorityName="Titterton &amp; Whatley" authorityYear="2005" box="[750,1347,692,717]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculanitida">
<emphasis box="[750,1044,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Xestoleberis maculanitida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Titterton" box="[1051,1347,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" refString="Titterton, R. &amp; Whatley, R. (2005) Recent marine ostracoda from the Solomon Islands. Part 2: Cytheracea, Xestoleberididae. Revista Espanola de Micropaleontologia, 37 (2), 291 - 313." type="journal article" year="2005">Titterton &amp; Whatley, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1362,1431,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1705,1727]" captionTargetBox="[173,1384,212,1665]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1684]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32552): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2. (B’) An 2 claws, (C) Md coxa, (D) Md palp, (E) Md exopodite, (M) Furca. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32550): (F) Mx palp and endites, (F’) Mx palp, (G) Mx branchial plate, (H) BO, (I) L 5, (J) L 6, (K) L 7, (L) Hp. Scale bars: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208334/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
, Nos. 15, 18, Pl. 3, 
<figureCitation box="[425,514,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[171,1392,240,1787]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,195,1815]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Xestoleberis petrosa n. sp. Male holotype (UMUT RA 32524): (A) An 1, (A’) An 1 terminating setae, (B) An 2, (B’) An 2 claws, (E) Mx, (E’) Mx palp, (F) BO, (J) Hp. Female paratype UMUT RA 32526): (C) Md coxa and palp, (D) Md exopodite, (G) L 5, (H) L 6, (I) L 7. Female paratype (UMUT RA 32527): (K) Furca. Scale bar: 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208339/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Figs. 9</figureCitation>
–16, 
<bibRefCitation author="Titterton" box="[583,915,727,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" refString="Titterton, R. &amp; Whatley, R. (2005) Recent marine ostracoda from the Solomon Islands. Part 2: Cytheracea, Xestoleberididae. Revista Espanola de Micropaleontologia, 37 (2), 291 - 313." type="journal article" year="2005">Titterton &amp; Whatley 2005</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1217,727,752]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann-Schroder, 1978" authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1978" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraporthedlandensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Xestoleberis paraporthedlandensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[405,699,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1978) Zur Kenntnis des Eulitorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 75, 63 - 219." type="journal article" year="1978">Hartmann-Schröder, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Abb. 409–422, Tafel XIII 
<figureCitation box="[1018,1126,764,789]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="1.[151,250,1304,1326]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,250,1833,1855]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,267,1272]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1430,1079,1773]" captionTargetId-0="figure@1.[151,1436,267,1282]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[149,1434,1037,1799]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. P 1 – P 6: present study specimen collection sites. B 1 – B 3: collection sites for Xestoleberis variegata and Xestoleberis curta by Brady (1890). Refer to Table 1 for site details. Color-coded circles indicating the geographical distribution of Fijian Xestoleberis species (seven new species described by the present paper and two species reported by Brady (1890 )). Ocean depth contours and the fast flowing Bligh Water currents are also illustrated." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Xestoleberis becca n. sp. Male holotype (A) RV, (B) LV (UMUT RA 32562). Xestoleberis concava n. sp. Female paratype (C) RV, (D) LV (UMUT RA 32550). Xestoleberis gracilariaii n. sp. Male holotype (E) RV, (F) LV (UMUT RA 32531). Xestoleberis marcula n. sp. Male holotype (G) RV, (H) LV (UMUT RA 32556). Xestoleberis natuvuensis n. sp. Female paratype (I) RV, (J) LV (UMUT RA 32543). Xestoleberis penna n. sp. Female paratype (K) RV, (L) LV (UMUT RA 32538). Xestoleberis petrosa n. sp. Male holotype (M) RV, (N) LV (UMUT RA 32524). Scale bar: 200 µm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/208331/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/208332/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[1140,1428,764,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1978) Zur Kenntnis des Eulitorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 75, 63 - 219." type="journal article" year="1978">Hartmann-Schröder 1978</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,319,799,824]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">Australia</collectingCountry>
. In contrast with the mostly straight and simple (and some trifurcate) anterior marginal pores of 
<taxonomicName class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculanitida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">X. maculanitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the anterior marginal pores of 
<taxonomicName box="[665,764,836,860]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becca">
<emphasis box="[665,764,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">X. becca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are branching with at most five branches. The ejaculatory duct arrangements of 
<taxonomicName box="[421,526,872,896]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becca">
<emphasis box="[421,526,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">X. becca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[598,884,872,896]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraporthedlandensis">
<emphasis box="[598,884,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">X. paraporthedlandensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vary. One of the Hp distal processes of 
<taxonomicName class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraporthedlandensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">X. paraporthedlandensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
terminates into a seta while neither of the distal processes of 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1198,908,932]" class="Ostracoda" family="Xestoleberididae" genus="Xestoleberis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becca" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1101,1198,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">X. becca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1207,1272,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1207,1272,908,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="329">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
possesses any seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
